&#8216;Madam and Eve, Take Us To Your Leader&#8217; sells for R160 For more than 23 years, Madam and Eve cartoons have brought a smile to the faces of thousands of avid South African newspaper readers. The interesting and funny dynamic between a housewife, her family and her domestic worker has kept a global audience entertained through a number of mediums. The latest coffee table book offering from Stephen Francis and Rico Madam and Eve, Take Us To Your Leader is laden with much-needed chuckles. It is smart, witty and deadly funny and has a fantastic mix of sitcom, satire and day-to-day new South Africa issues. The paperback sells for R160 and is published by Jacana Media. Alvin Reeves Share on Facebook Share Share on Twitter Tweet Share on Google Plus Share